ENTRY       EC 2.4.1.319                Enzyme
NAME        beta-1,4-mannooligosaccharide phosphorylase;
            RaMP2
CLASS       Transferases;
            Glycosyltransferases;
            Hexosyltransferases
SYSNAME     1,4-beta-D-mannooligosaccharide:phosphate alpha-D-mannosyltransferase
REACTION    [(1->4)-beta-D-mannosyl]n + phosphate = [(1->4)-beta-D-mannosyl]n-1 + alpha-D-mannose 1-phosphate
SUBSTRATE   [(1->4)-beta-D-mannosyl]n;
            phosphate [CPD:C00009]
PRODUCT     [(1->4)-beta-D-mannosyl]n-1;
            alpha-D-mannose 1-phosphate [CPD:C00636]
COMMENT     The enzyme, isolated from the ruminal bacterium Ruminococcus albus, catalyses the reversible phosphorolysis of beta-1,4-mannooligosaccharide with a minimum size of three monomers.
HISTORY     EC 2.4.1.319 created 2014
REFERENCE   1  [PMID:23093406]
